{"word":"κοινός","slug":"κοινός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϰοινός, ή, όν</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fr.\">fr.</a> a root to which <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> cum ‘with’ is related]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp></b> ‘shared collectively’, <b>in common, shared <a href='B:510 2:44'>Ac 2:44</a>; <a href='B:630 1:4'>Tit 1:4</a>; <a href='B:720 1:1'>Jd 3</a>.<p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘belonging to what is everyday’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp> ordinary <a href='B:650 10:29'>Hb 10:29</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp> common</b> = contrary to special cultic practice or perspective <b><a href='B:480 7:2'>Mk 7:2</a>, <a href='B:480 7:5'>5</a>; <a href='B:510 10:14'>Ac 10:14</a>; <a href='B:520 14:14'>Ro 14:14</a>; <a href='B:730 21:27'>Rv 21:27</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:κοίμησις\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:κοινόω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}